## Analysis of baseline game (AlphaCyborgPolicy, seed default, 5000 steps)
- Score: 3.07
- 205 junctions aligned, 123 lost to ship scrambling
- 4 aligners (agents 0,1,2,4): 47+52+44+61 = 204 alignments
- 1 scrambler (agent 3): 123 scrambles
- 3 miners (agents 5,6,7): 6 deaths combined
- Heart economy: 356 total hearts generated, ~386 theoretical max (bottleneck: oxygen at 2704)
- Each aligner averages ~51 alignments / 5000 steps = 1 alignment per 98 steps (slow!)
- Theoretical minimum alignment cycle: ~31 steps. Actual is 3x slower.
- Running 5-seed comparison: AlphaCyborg vs V65TrueReplica

## Key bottleneck analysis
- Alignment rate: 0.041/step, Scramble rate: 0.0246/step, Net: 0.0164/step
- To get score >10: need ~10+ avg aligned junctions held throughout
- Need either more aligners, faster cycle, or less scramble loss
- Scramblers: 123 hearts used for scrambling = could be 123 more alignments instead
- Plan: test 5-aligner / 0-scrambler variant (AlphaNoScramblePolicy)

## 5-seed comparison results (5000 steps each)
- RealignBoost: avg 3.84 (1.73, 2.05, 1.96, 5.49, 7.98) — BEST
- V65True: avg 3.37 (4.11, 2.10, 1.92, 3.43, 5.30)
- AlphaCyborg: avg 2.04 (4.40, 2.84, 1.12, 0.00, 1.86)
- NoScramble: avg 1.42 (1.91, 0.98, 1.40, 0.00, 2.83) — WORST

## Key findings
- RealignBoost (re-alignment bonus) is best, confirming the approach
- V65 targeting outperforms AlphaCyborg (hub_penalty > stable budgets)
- NoScramble (removing scramblers with base targeting) actually HURTS performance
- Seed 4 causes AlphaCyborg/NoScramble to score 0.00 (all agents die). V65True/RealignBoost handle it fine.
- Created AlphaV65NoScrambleBoostPolicy: V65Realign + no scramblers
- Running tests: V65NoScrambleBoost and V65Realign

